3. Suryadeva's provenance 
References made by Suryadeva in his Laghumānasa-vyakhyā go to show that he was a native of the Cola country in South India and -Wrote at Gangāpura or Gangăpurī, which may be identified with Gangai-konda-Colapuram (lat 11° 13' N, long. 79° 30' E), on the basis of astronomical observations made at this place recorded by Suryadeva himself. Thus, under Laghumānasa, II. 1, he states that the equinoctial midday shadow at Gangāpura is 27 angulas which corresponds to the latitude of 11°.3. So also the ascensional differences and times of risings of the signs also correspond to this place, 3 Sūryadeva also 
